The Czech economy stagnated compared to the Vorquartal, Germany and France.
The bonds market snaps today, but all the records.
Investors keep not only Greece but also Spain, France, Austria and other countries.
The statistical office of the Euro-zone, Germany, the Czech Republic and some other European countries have published their preliminary forecasts about the economic development in the third quarter.
GDP grew by Germany's expected 0.5% of France by 0.4%.
Both countries at the same time to revise their data for the second quarter, in which Germany recorded a higher growth than was initially expected (0.3% growth instead of the predicted 0.1%), while France, a slight decline of 0.1% admitted (original claims only spoke of stagnation).
The Czech economy grew in this year's third quarter compared with the previous year to 1.5 percent.
Compared to the Vorquartal GDP stagnated, however, and, according to political. Statistical Office confirmed the trend of the slowdown of economic performance.
The results are worse than the forecasts of analysts.
The main events:
The Czech economy grew in this year's third quarter compared with the previous year to 1.5 percent, compared to the previous quarter it stagnated, however.
According to preliminary and seasonal überrechneten claims the German economy grew in the third quarter by 0.5 percent.
Throughout the euro zone and the EU economy between July and September compared with the previous quarter growth by 0.2 percent, in line with the expectations of analysts.
The Greek economy shrank compared with the previous year by 5.2 percent.
The return on their 10-year government bonds climbed the value of 28.45%.
