IBM history: space flights from cheese Schneider
The one hundred years ago, society founded in New York, IBM (International Business Machines) initially had a rather complicated names - computing Tabulating Recording Corporation.
The name IBM took until 1924 - it was originally a brand name for a plant in Canada and South America.
The foundation stone for subsequent IBM society, the merger of four companies, whose history in the 1980s of the 19th century.
They owned technologies such as the famous Stechkartenuhren registration of work begins and ends.
The architects of this new company was Charles Ranlett Flint, until 1930, the chair of the board.
And it was Flint, the head of the competition, the company stopped Thomas J. Watson, so that helped him in the management of the company.
This Leader was the founder of IBM in the shade - Watson's ideas based until today, the invincible culture and identity of the company.
Watson led the company until 1952.
IBM began, as the name betrays the manufacture and distribution of all sorts of machinery for the trade of sausages and cheese tailors to cash.
In the first four decades in which Watson led the company, he doubled their sales to $9 million and the company expanded, and on all continents.
Watson was so essential to the company that he was all for forty years in the head, then he was replaced by his son, Thomas Watson junior.
Under whose stewardship IBM began to work on the development of artificial intelligence and developed the first Programmiersprache.
In the 1960s helped technicians and computer from IBM, NASA to launch flights into space - Mercury and Saturn, and the famous flight of people to the moon in 1969.
Meanwhile, IBM developed the first computer family with the same computer architecture - the number of IBM System/360 in 1964.
A classic PC, the computer-certain standards of the time, came in 1981 under the IBM 5150 names on the market.
Twenty years later, IBM sold its computer production to the Chinese company Lenovo, on the other hand, they bought the Konsultanten part of the company, PricewaterhouseCoopers and rose entirely in the business with Consulting benefits and services with high added value.
The strategy, IBM is paying off in the last three years, the concept of ' Smarter Planet. "
It embodies the intention to use technologies intelligent in hitherto not planned areas, for example, to improve the situation in transport and urban management.
In the commercial sector, IBM recently led the dealers to help the entire commercial cycle to guide the platform ' Smarter commerce. "
IBM is also in the Czech Republic, a strong story.
Already, in 1932, IBM founded a branch in the former Czechoslovakia - even the first country in Central and Eastern Europe.
Today, IBM ČR, among other things, it is also a strategic outsourcing Center in Brno.
The Centre for Central and Eastern Europe, devolve in Prague and is also a top team of researchers from world-class that deals with the technology of voting identification.
