In June 1998, joined by two of the three major Swiss banks to a huge corporation.
There was a bank when the merger was too big for the small Swiss - and grew.
It helped that the two different precursor-supplemented banks UBS: a rich, but sleepy bank with a focus on asset management in Zurich and poorer, but more internationalized.
Suddenly the internationalised favourable investment bankers at a lot of money, they were able to turn a huge wheel.
Two names are associated with the rise of the UBS: Peter Wuffli, from 2001 to 2007, the group's head of UBS, Marcel Ospel, the chairman of the board.
"I always thought Wuffli and Ospel are a dream team," says banking researcher Hans Geiger.
"Wuffli, higher intellectual, modest, a lot of models and statistics, and Ospel, the belly man has worked from the bank lesson to the very top."
But Ospel was finally left to Wuffli.
And Wuffli have probably made a crucial mistake at the end: "he thought his models are the reality," says Geiger.
"It is a tragic case."
Tragic, perhaps.
It is clear: frolic came before the fall.
UBS employees remember clearly the leadership meetings where company chief Wuffli the same purported slogan: Goldman Sachs from the throne.
The American bank was the most powerful investment bank in the world.
They led the League Tables, " rankings, which documented the success of the banks of the time.
In the meantime, the UBS, according to the top.
Some steps were already succeeded.
In the foreign exchange business and equity trading, she played at the top.
Corporate advisers who have been charged, but a weakness: international business interest in the language of bankers ' Fixed-income, " there is a huge gap with the largest banks.
The UBS have gaps in US mortgage products.
In order to close this gap, UBS went into an adventure that almost cost the existence.
Hungry for growth, invested both the bank itself, as well as a liberating in their hedge funds in the US sub-prime assets.
It became a huge machine, packaged securities on American mortgage loans and reached - but also maintained risks.
Also, when other banks exit.
"In the summer of 2007, when the US housing market was going up in flames, UBS has bought," says banking expert Geiger.
The euphoria is so deep.
A manager to go after the other, more difficult than the attempts to clean up than thought.
Posts in UBS were Schleudersitz and shaky until today.
Whoever leads the large bank now has an almost impossible job.
He needs to find a strategy for a bank, which lost all obvious business models.
Banks researchers Geiger has an idea: stop the investment banking, concentrating on asset management, return to the Swiss roots.
So far, the bank will not (yet).
But the investment banking to shrink, so much is already clear.
On Thursday, the new bank chief Sergio Ermotti to imagine his future strategy in the world.
The 51-year-old Italo-Swiss was only intended as a temporary solution, as the bank is surprisingly separated from predecessor Grübel.
Meanwhile, he has pushed through: he should lead the business of UBS, the Zurich bank announced on Tuesday.
Ermotti wants the investment bank to back in the mid-1990s.
He is cutting 3500 jobs.
But that is not enough.
The UBS needs a vision.
Who is it?
They want to earn money?
These are the questions that Axel Weber sure now.
Publicly, he says only that he and his wife, once an apartment in Zurich.
Next year.
