"Nobody wants to see that the euro zone remains unstable and turbulent," he said.
"We are facing huge challenges and we need to maintain a high growth level."
"It is not an option, it is a mandate, because where else we find work for millions of young men and women."
Others argue that developing economies such as India have no reason to help the rich Europeans, when they are facing great economic challenges.
