Lee Howell, executive director of the World Economic Forum, similar asked why India's reserves should be used to keep in Greece the numerous and well-paid employees in the public sector, with jobs in poorly led losses bring institutions such as the railways.
Mr Nag said that the crisis in the eurozone "significant knock-on effects" on the whole of Asia.
The ADB forecast, with economic growth at 7.5 per cent in Asia for the years 2011/now threatens "the risk of gradation" because of the threat from Europe.
He said vulnerable emerging markets should produce "contingency plans" in order to protect themselves in a downward trend and a significant capital outflow of their word.
