"They must contribute nearly 12 million, and although the year comes to an end, they have given us a penny."
The court approved for 2015, the transition to digital television in Mexico
The conversion of the analogue to digital signals in the last few years, the world's most important changes.
The Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) rejected the constitutional complaints must be brought forward by the Senate and House against the presidential decree and by virtue of the switch from analogue to digital signals from 2021 to 2015, due to a lack of eight votes needed for legislative challenge.
A minority of four ministers, including the President of the Supreme Court, Juan Silva Meza was the view of the president, Felipe Calderón, have not exceeded his powers when he described the decree law with the details of the switch to the terrestrial digital television.
This decision was rejected by the Senate launched constitutional dispute, since he received the necessary qualified majority of eight votes, so that the court should decide on the constitutionality or the non-constitutionality; the law remains in force.
In the project for the lawsuit, which was drafted by the Minister Olga Sanchez Cordero, has been proposed to explain the decree law unconstitutional because, for the radio and television concerned the Comisión Federal de Telecomunicaciones (Cofetel) (Federale Telecommunications Commission in Mexico) is responsible, which is why the decree law reserved for the hierarchical principles and the law would contradict.
Voted in favor of the project only Zaldivar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sánchez Cordero.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies constitutional complaints against the decree law. After the adoption of the complaints, the Minister Sánchez Cordero said the decree law no longer and all activities to create the digital transmission.
The Council of Ministers also rejected the complaint filed by the Chamber of Deputies, without entering into the debate on the project, which is also the Minister Sánchez Cordero was responsible.
In his speech, the Prime Minister, not to agree with the arguments of the project, in the sense that the government of countries with general rules, the measures should take the public administration, should regulate.
"I do not believe that, if we do that, it would impair the independence of the regulator." She also recalled that the strategic planning policy areas, such as the sector of telecommunications, for constitutional reasons, the central state government, since it leads the state affairs.
The replacement of analogue signals through digital is one of the most important changes that has taken place in recent years throughout the world, and it leads to a better use of the radio-electric spectrum, increasing the quality of the signal and more channels.
Delaying the switch, she said, was a beneficiary of the digitisation, which have a decision in the public interest, not just the technical aspects, "because they include economic, social, political and technical aspects of security."
These matters, she emphasized, "the action of the whole system, in accordance with the principle of economic management by the state, they included a group of characteristics in the hands of the central state government."
She called that many countries around the world, the digital conversion had already been carried out, and the government, even though they had highly specialised facilities.
We could not conclude that the government, with the publication of the contested law decree to intervene in the powers of Congress, because the laws passed by the legislature would be respected, " she assured.
The opportunity to recount ballots in Michoacán individually is considered
According to the data of PREP is the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor's nearly 27 percent, with 879 votes not yet counted a total of 6074.
The possibility of individual counting of ballots is not yet counted in this year's elections in Michoacán a reality, because the Programa de Resultados electrica oral Preliminares (PREP) issued data is the difference between the first and second place in the gubernatorial elections nearly 27 percent, with 879 votes, out of a total of 6074.
In this sense, the President of the Consejo General del Instituto Electoral de Michoacán (IEM), María de Los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that just adopted last November 9, the election of a series of regulations on the harmonisation of local rules with the reforms of the federal states in election matters.
It is worth remembering that Michoacán neither his political constitution nor his electoral law nor its law on the election of justice had adapted to the reforms adopted by Congress in this round of elections so that they were not entered into force, and the governor Leonel Godoy Rangel avoided their publication in the State Gazette within the deadlines with the argument to have any objections.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) on the constitutional complaint filed by the local legislature, and vice versa, the voice of the state to the constitutional reforms as "invalid and illegal" because it did not have the right to "decide or veto it."
María de Los Ángeles Llanderal said in an interview about the possibility of individual recount that, thanks to the adoption of the directives by the Consejo General del IEM the possibility that the local election authority partially or fully counting the ballot papers.
So under the following conditions contained in one or several election packages votes will be counted partial results in the protocols do not agree; the protocol on the counting of votes and berechnung is no files or it is not in possession of the chairman of the electoral commission or there are obvious errors or modifications in the protocols.
Moreover, the total count of fully busy ballot papers if there is a difference between the alleged winners and the second place, which is equal to or less than one percent is provided at the beginning of the session is an explicit request from the Party or coalition chairman, the second of the candidate.
The counting of votes can also be done in their entirety, if after the conclusion of the proper calculation that the difference between the alleged winners and candidates in the second, or less than one percent, provided it is an explicit request from a representative of the party, whose candidate has become the second, in this case, the election packages were exposed to a partial recount were excluded.
It is worth noting that the elections in Morelia in the same situation, where according to PREP the difference between the first and second place just 0.16%, although the 129 votes not yet counted a total of 923 election protocols.
